# Documentation Rules

- **Location**: Keep all architectural and project specification documentation inside the `/docs` folder (e.g., `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/PROJECT_SPEC.md`).
- **Minimal Root Docs**: The root directory should contain only:
  - `README.md` (general info, install, folder tree, license)
  - `LICENSE` (MIT)
  - `AGENTS.md` (AI instructions)
- **Formatting**: Format all documents using standard Github Flavored Markdown. Avoid wrapping lines unnecessarily.
- **Maintain Content**: Never overwrite or delete meaningful sections of documentation unless explicitly requested.
